This if you click on "Preview", after any price calculation, you can see some preview renders.

And if you want to know how the settings change the price, here is the basics:

Resolution:
The render time and price of a project scales roughly quadratically with the resolution. So that means doubling the resolution can cause the price to go 4x.

Cycles samples:
The price roughly scales linearly with the samples setting. Doubling the samples can double the price, halving the samples halves the price.

Render time hours / deadline:
The shorter the render time, the more servers we need, so it gets more expensive. But this all depends on the current server availability. If there are plenty of servers free in our cheapest data centers, the price stays low. If the deadline is so tight that we need to resort to servers in more expensive datacenters, the price might spike upwards more quickly.

Hope that helps. If you have any questions about this, feel free to shoot us a reply!

